song.title: The Greatest

annotations:
And that’s the strangest part
 At the bottom of a wasted heart
 With all that room to fall
 The greatest love of all

Though Sasami feels as though her heart is completely useless and damaged which could have been caused by a past relationship, she still acknowledges the fact that her ‘wasted heart’ is still capable of loving and is filled with an immense love

Baby, I’d never turn away
 In your arms I’d forever stay

Here, Sasami enumerates on her desperation to stay with the songs intended significant other, even though they might be hurting her in the longer run. She is longing for intimacy and a connection with this partner, hoping that they’d never turn her away, and will stay in their arms forever.
